history.content: I'd say 161 is much more practical than 188 and therefore more likely to be applicable in an internship, but in reality you likely won't use concepts from either of these in a general SWE internship. You will read/write more code in more languages in 161, so if you aren't currently comfortable in your coding skills I'd say go with 161. If you're comfortable, then I'd say pick whichever interests you more. Good luck, both are great classes!

How useful is 161 for the work you do in internships as a SWE intern? That’s really the only reason I’m considering it over 188; I’m fairly certain that I’ll have a less time-consuming semester if I take 188 instead. My interest in both subject matters is equally pretty low (I’m a junior so don’t have that many CS class options left). Thanks!
history.subject: CS 152+161 vs 152+188?
